author: Bellular News
description:
Game of the Year. 50 developers. $10 million. Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 just proved what a small team can do. But they weren't the only ones who tried. Ex-AAA devs have been striking out on their own for years. Some had legendary pedigrees. Some had hundreds of millions in funding. Some had both. 

Most of them failed. This is what 2025 taught us about what it actually takes to win.
